  <h1>DutyLog Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> July 9, 2026</p>

  <p>DutyLog respects your privacy. This app is designed to help users track work hours, shifts, and job entries without collecting personal data.</p>

  <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>DutyLog does not collect, store, or share personal information from users.</p>

  <h2>Data Storage</h2>
  <p>All app data, including work entries and settings, is stored locally on the user’s device unless otherwise stated in a future app update.</p>

  <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>DutyLog does not use third-party analytics, advertising SDKs, or external account systems at this time.</p>

  <h2>Children’s Privacy</h2>
  <p>DutyLog does not knowingly collect personal information from children.</p>

  <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
  <p>This Privacy Policy may be updated in the future if app functionality changes. Any updates will be reflected on this page.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, you can contact the developer at: your-email@example.com</p>
